rComments: very cool professor, who's passionate about digital media and the CCIT program. One of the nicest most entertaining profs I've ever had during my academic career and I encourage anyone in the CCIT major to take all of his lectures!!! guaranteed you will be engaged in the material and will most likely get a good mark !
The lec is 9am and I commute, I usually don't bother going to early morning classes, but I actually wake up extra early to go to Prof. Caraway's class so there's that

Professor Caraway is super chill, you can tell he actually cares about his students. He does whatever he can to make things easier on us. His assignments are clear, and straightforward and his lectures are interesting. He's funny and wants you to succeed.

I was really worried before taking this course because, i know absolutely nothing about law. But Brett made this course interesting and easy. He cares a lot about his students, TAKE THIS CLASS WITH HIM

Caraway is my favourite professor I've had at UTM. He is funny and easy to listen to. He made a 9am lecture enjoyable, which says a lot. For a professor in such an unorganized program, he is fantastic. I'd recommend him without a doubt; he doesn't post slides but honestly you're better off attending lecture because he provides hints for the exams.

I've never taken a civics or law course before so I was pretty clueless about law walking into the lecture hall for the first time but Brett made law concepts in CCT206 very easy to understand. His lectures are hilarious and he relates his jokes back to course concepts. I usually skip my 9am lectures but I never skipped a single lecture of Brett's.

Prof Caraway is one of the best prof I've had in my 3 years at UTM. He really knows how to engage with his audience, he makes 9am lectures not only bearable but fun and entertaining. I highly recommend taking a class with him if you can, he has definitely enhanced by University experience.
Such an amazing prof. Makes every minute of a two hour lecture interesting.
Dude is LIT! Highly recommend him. Enjoyed the class tremendously.

This was one of my favourite classes to attend. Brett was always enthusiastic about the subject material, which helped make for a consistently warm, welcoming, inclusive, and exciting class discussion dynamic, even at 9:00PM on a winter evening.
He's by far the best professor I have ever had and made economics make sense
By far THE BEST professor I've ever had. Would take any course if he's the instructor honestly. Incredibly helpful and amaaaaaaaaaaazing.

I absolutely loved Prof. Caraway! He gave great, easy to follow lectures, and made them pretty entertaining. He's really funny and approachable, so don't hesitate to ask questions. Assignments and tests weren't too difficult and the expectations were clear. Would definitely take any of his classes again.
Awesome lectures and nice guy! Heavier on the assignments but grading criteria is clear and not too tough.
CCT109 was my favourite class! I absolutely loved it. Brett makes it a lot easier and more entertaining during lectures.

CCT109 was the one class I really looked forward to attending each week. The lectures were easy to follow along and I found the topics we discussed very interesting. Prof Caraway is great at what he does, if I could re-take this course I definitely would :)
Brett is a cool prof. He's pretty funny, which helps makes lectures more interesting and he isn't too uptight about anything. Overall a great prof and I'd take any of his courses.
Awesome Prof! :)
Best prof  I had! He's amazing!

rComments: Hands down the best professor I've ever had. Very clear in his lectures, explains topics well, makes sure people understand what is going on as well as what is expected of them. Very accessible as well, responds to emails quickly and is overall a great person to talk to and learn from. Would take any of his courses.

One of the best profs I've had the pleasure of studying under. He breaks down incredibly complex subject matter into base concepts and throws in personal experiences to keep the class interested.  Very down to earth and will help students with any problems, whether academic in nature or not. Tests and assignments are fair and encourage growth.

His class was one of the few ones I looked forward to attending on a weekly basis. He's a nicer version of Sheldon Cooper, minus all the meh traits. Tests are fairly straightforward and he provides clear study guides. Very helpful and friendly.
Great prof.
Such an amazing teacher!!! class was alway's full and full of laughter.  Very clear and to the point with lectures. Make 4 hour courses fly by!!! would take any class of his again!!

Proff Caraway is one of my favs at UTM. He is very helpful and responds to emails SO fast. Lectures are interesting, but (like any first year class) are very generalized and broad. I would defiantly take another clss with him.
He really knows how to engage the audience. His lectures are crystal clear and he can explain topics well.
